# Team Topologies Overlay

When the user requests a Team Topologies health assessment, use this framework as your lens. Team Topologies shifts focus from individual team behaviours to team design, cognitive load, and interaction patterns as the primary levers of organisational health.

---

## Core Team Topologies Concepts

### Four Fundamental Team Types
| Type | Purpose | Healthy signs | Warning signs |
|------|---------|--------------|--------------|
| **Stream-aligned** | Deliver value on a single stream of work end-to-end | Fast flow, high autonomy, minimal external dependencies | Doing platform/enabling work themselves; blocked by other teams; too broad a scope |
| **Platform** | Reduce cognitive load for stream-aligned teams via self-service capabilities | Teams adopt the platform willingly; platform enables rather than gates | Bureaucratic approval processes; platform teams as bottlenecks; low adoption |
| **Enabling** | Help stream-aligned teams acquire new capabilities | Short-lived engagements; teams become self-sufficient; facilitating not doing | Long-term dependency on enabling team; doing the work instead of upskilling |
| **Complicated Subsystem** | Manage high cognitive-load specialist components | Clear ownership; minimal direct interaction required | Over-reliance on subsystem team; knowledge hoarding; bottleneck formation |

### Three Interaction Modes
| Mode | Description | When healthy | When not |
|------|-------------|-------------|---------|
| **Collaboration** | Two teams work closely together, often temporarily | Active co-creation; diverging toward independence | Permanent collaboration; unclear ownership; neither team learning |
| **X-as-a-Service** | One team consumes another's service with minimal interaction | Consumer team is unblocked; service is self-serve | Service team is a constant bottleneck; requires too much hand-holding |
| **Facilitating** | Enabling team helps a stream-aligned team acquire capability | Stream-aligned team becomes self-sufficient; enabling team moves on | Enabling team becomes permanent; dependency persists |

