## Team Type Health Indicators

### Stream-Aligned Team (most common)
🟢 Healthy: Clear value stream; end-to-end delivery capability; minimal cross-team coordination required; fast flow; customer connection
🟡 Developing: Some scope creep into platform/enabling work; moderate dependencies; customer connection indirect
🔴 At Risk: Doing work across multiple value streams; chronic dependencies; can't release independently; no customer connection

### Platform Team
🟢 Healthy: Teams adopt willingly; self-service; reduces cognitive load; clear roadmap driven by stream-aligned team needs
🟡 Developing: Some bottleneck tendencies; partial self-service; adoption uneven
🔴 At Risk: Approval gate for everything; teams route around platform; building for its own sake not for consumers

### Enabling Team
🟢 Healthy: Short-lived engagements; teams become self-sufficient; moves on
🟡 Developing: Engagements running longer than planned; some skill transfer happening
🔴 At Risk: Permanent fixture; doing the work instead of upskilling; dependency growing

